               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18631026-name-395" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18631026-name-395" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18631026-name-395" type="surname" value="HAMMOND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18631026-name-395" type="given" value="JEREMIAH"></interp>JEREMIAH HAMMOND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a porter, and live at 22, De Beauvoir-square, Kingsland-road—on 26th September, I was in Farringdon-street; my wife was in Mr. Simpson's shop, and I was standing opposite the door, waiting for her—the prisoner and another female went up to the door, took a parcel, and walked off with it, under her arm—I went to the door, and told the shop-walker.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> It is false. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> It is not—the party with you was obliged to hold up the pile to keep it from falling, as you took it from the centre not from the top.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18631026-name-396" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18631026-name-396" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
